name: Quinsigamond Community College
directions: In the Suprenant building, between the Faculty Lounge and Faculty Offices on the first floor.  The faculty rooms are locked, so you'll need someone to let you in.
comment: The bathroom is technically for faculty and staff only, but if the faculty rooms are open, or if the right people are there, you can use it.  Due to too many doors, the bathroom is most likely not wheelchair accessible.

name: Climb 306
comment: If you aren't there to climb, then just ask to use washroom.

name: Truffle Pigs Cafe
directions: Enter into the store part and take a left at the desk.  2 clearly-marked gender-free washrooms.  Food there is pretty good too. JTI

name: Fuse
directions: All the bathrooms are unisex but have urinals around the corner. Also, cool reasturant

name: South Valley UU Society
directions: Building is locked, ring bell for access. Genderfree bathroom is in back annex. (There are gendered bathrooms in the basement.) Ask for directions.  Minister and other employees are trans.
comment: Open Sunday mornings for services, plus Monday 9-12, Tue 10-2, Wed 2-9, Thu 10 -2. Call at other times. 944-9723

name: Central Park
directions: To the right of the basketball courts, to the left of the skatepark. Right before the baseball field, cant miss it.
comment: Great bathroom if you really need to poop. It's open to the public but rarely will anyone intrude on you as you drop the deuce. Highly recommended from an experienced user.

name: Barnes & Noble
directions: top floor at the top of the escalator by the cafe
comment: 2 locking gendered bathrooms

name: Pizzeria Paradiso
directions: One accessible genderfree locking bathroom on the first floor. Two non-accessible gendered locking bathrooms on the lower level by the bar.
comment: It's in a restaurant.

name: Alameda Marketplace
directions: Entrance is off the bakery.

name: Rockridge Market Hall
directions: The key is hanging on a hook near the cooler in the Bakery section of the market. The bathrooms are actually right next door to the bakery, through the door and down the hall.

name: Woodstar
directions: From Main Street in Northampton, going away from King/Pleasant Street, it will be on the right on Masonic Street, passing by Packard's, before Bela Vegetarian restaurant.

name: Jack London Square
directions: Foot of Broadway where it meets Jack London Square, next to the parking garage and Barnes & Noble.
comment: Not sure how late it is open.

name: Willow Canyon Outdoor
directions: rear of the bookstore.

name: Subway Sandwiches & Salads
comment: on route 140

name: Dunkin Donuts
directions: Depending on which door you walk in, it's either to your right or straight and to the left. Just ask an employee if you really can't find it, they'll point it out to you.

name: Ray's Place
comment: Great Vietnamese restaurant in Spenard with wonderful inexpensive soup and two gender-free restrooms.

name: Triumph Brewing Company
directions: First floor, in the back, up and around the little ramp on the left.
comment: Pretty cool bathroom.  It's set up more like a dressing room than a bathroom.  You walk into a general area, then there are probably 10 self-contained stalls (toilet and sink).

name: Grand Valley State University AuSable Hall
street: AuSable Hall, Grand Valley State University
directions: 2nd floor in corridor full of Psychology faculty offices - walk toward the window full of plants and the bathroom will be on the left
comment: The building is open weekdays from @7am-10PM

name: Valero Gas Station
directions: Take the Appian Way exit off of I-80, can't miss it; it's on the corner.  Walk in the sliding doors and go left past the snacks.  There are two stalls for woman.  Pretty clean for a gas station.
comment: Great stop before reaching the city.  They're open late!

name: Glen's Market
directions: As you walk into the store you'll be facing the end of the check out lanes. Turn left and the bathroom is in the corner on your left.
comment: Store is open 24 hours. The bathroom is single occupant genderfree. It's often rather dirty so use at your own risk ;)

name: Stetson's
directions: Up on the second floor of the bar the bathroom is a single stall and has both M/F icons on the door.
comment: There was a bit of a line, but the crowd there was pretty laidback for a college bar crowd.

name: Cafe Los Cuiles
directions: by the counter, kitchen area
comment: clean and nice. a cafe with decent snacks, vegetarian fare and lots of nice students!

name: Chapel Hill
directions: Right in, to the right.

name: Mendel Art Gallery
directions: Top floor near the eating area. Hours 9-9 daily

name: Ferry Bldg
directions: Top of Market.

name: Nordstroms
comment: Each stall is it's own individual room!  And a luxurious lounge area to chill out and primp.  Love it.

name: Nordstroms
comment: Each stall is it's own individual room!  And a luxurious lounge area to chill out and primp.  Love it.

name: Build-A-Bear Workshop
directions: To the very back of the store, behind the 'Dress Me' section.
comment: If you can stand the kiddies & families, this a great, clean place to pee in the mall that has single-stall, genderfree bathrooms.

name: Flavour Cafe
directions: Slightly behind and to the right of the cash register.
comment: Gay-owned, queer friendly establishment with great coffee, snacks & food!  Hosts local events, exhibits local art, has free book swap and free WiFi.  All around great place!

name: Honest Weight Food Co-Op
directions: Through Front Door, hang a left, next to the sevice desk
comment: hours are 7 am to 8 pm everday but sunday which is  9 am to 7 pm. good food too! and fun!

name: midstate Medical Center
directions: Emergency waiting room bathrooms are gender neutral

name: Starbucks
directions: At the corner of Winnetka and Ventura near Ralphs.
comment: Close by 9:30pm most nights but has a good GLBTQ friendly staff. Bathrooms are to the left of the hand-off bar.

name: Mangiare
directions: The bathroom is in a little hallway on the back wall to the right of the long service counter. A little computer desk is near the hallway's entrance.
comment: Mangiare is a restaurant. Its Yelp page:http://www.yelp.com/biz/0Z_0xrSi9yAA4I4fBm0T0g

name: Goodwill
comment: There are two locking doors, with signs on the doors that are both male and female.  It's off of Route 29, which is what most of Charlottesville is based off of, anyway, so it's never too far from where you are.

name: Mother Earth's Storehouse
directions: Enter mall, look for Mother Earth's Storehouse. There is a sign on the outside of the building - it's on the side with Modell's, to the right of Fashion Bug. There are two gender neutral bathrooms in the back of the store, to the right of the deli.

name: Affirmations Community Center
directions: Enter on 9 mile or from parking lot in back.  Gender Inclusive Restroom is on the lower level.
comment: Monday-Wednesday 9am-9pmThursday 9am-11pmFriday-Saturday 9am-12Midnightwww.goaffirmations.org

name: Affirmations Community Center
directions: Enter on 9 mile or from parking lot in back.  Gender Inclusive Restroom is on the lower level.
comment: Monday-Wednesday 9am-9pmThursday 9am-11pmFriday-Saturday 9am-12Midnightwww.goaffirmations.org

name: Jewel-Osco
directions: Front left corner of the store, by the pharmacy.
comment: 24-hour.

name: FLITE (Ferris State University's) Library
directions: It's in the basement, it might take some looking to find it.

name: Stony Brook Union
directions: On the main floor, to the left of the information desk.
comment: This used to be an employee only bathroom, but is now a gender-neutral single occupancy bathroom open to anyone. It's occasionally still locked by mistake; if that happens just ask whoever's working the info desk to unlock it.

name: Beard Papa
directions: by the counter
comment: has one of those coded doors. you must buy something to use it :(

name: The Crepe House
directions: up by the counter, one single stall gender neutral bathroom.

name: Loblaws (Maple Leaf Gardens)
directions: On the ground floor, you go past the cash registers and there are 3 gender neutral, accessible washrooms.

name: Utah Pride Center
directions: They are in the TINT (youth section) on the south side of the parking lot.  These bathrooms are for folks 14-20 years old.  Other gender neutral bathrooms are between the middle meeting room and multi-purpose rooms.  These are usually locked unless you are there for a meeting.  If in doubt, use the free ones in the cafe!
comment: This is just about as queer friendly as you can get..

name: King's English Bookstore
directions: First floor, near the back.

name: Little Sister's Book & Art Emporium
comment: Little Sister's is open from 10 am to 11 pm. You need to ask for the key from one of their staff.

name: Humboldt State University
directions: NHE entire biulding, located next to the health at the library circle entrance.  Also genderfree at the multicultural center House 55 Laurel St.
comment: Located on a university campus, usually open until well into the evening 11pmish?

name: Martsa on Elm
comment: Tibetan restaurant. One restroom, ungen dered.

name: Harvard Law School - Austin Hall
directions: walk in the main door and turn left. turn left again till you see the staircase or elevator.  go to the 3rd floor.  bathroom is on the landing.
comment: it's all law school offices near the bathroom, but the bathroom is public to the school. always clean. as long as people are  respectful of the space as a working environment and they are just in and out, it is unlikely anyone will ask any questions.

name: Red Fez
directions: one bathroom on first floor near the kitchen. second bathroom on second floor between the bar and pinball machine
comment: 2 genderfree, single stall, locking bathrooms.

name: Tazza Cafe
directions: to the left of the coffee/drinks bar area
comment: 2 genderfree, single stall, locking bathrooms.

name: Atticus Book Store
directions: main floor, back right hand corner.
comment: open until 10, I think.

name: java monkey
directions: In the back; single-stall/locking

name: waffle house
directions: Go in the door and through the swinging door to the left.
comment: 24 hours, as far as i know.

name: South Center Mall
directions: Restroom entrance in the food court (Best Buy entrance).  Family lounge is to the left.  There is one gender free locking bathroom on the right side of the lounge.
comment: Nice roomy bathroom with sink and mirror included inside.

name: South Center Mall
directions: Restroom entrance in the food court (Best Buy entrance).  Family lounge is to the left.  There is one gender free locking bathroom on the right side of the lounge.
comment: Nice roomy bathroom with sink and mirror included inside.

name: ASU smith-wright hall
street: on campus between rankin science and the library
directions: 3rd floor, middle of the hall
comment: specifically labled as a transgender bathroom!!  our psychology department is awesome!

name: 814 Club
comment: Gay Bar with drag shows on Sunday nights

name: University of Wisconsin-Milwaukee
directions: The Student Union EG75A & EG75B. It is on the ground floor east of the ATM machines, right before the Post newspaper office.

name: San Francisco Public Library - Main
directions: Bathrooms are on the lower level, behind the stairway.  If entering on Grove, go down the stairs or spiral ramp before you get to the security gates.
comment: There are two sets of bathrooms, the lower level ones described, and another set after you pass through security, just past the elevators.  Security just means you're not stealing any books, so no worries going through it.

name: Mohawk Service Station
directions: Sign says "Washrooms", but when you walk through the door there is only a single non-gendered lockable washroom.
comment: Kinda dirty, but otherwise okay.

name: Xtra Mart
directions: enter the Xtra Mart and go to the rear, left of the Xtra Mart portion of the store (Subway and Honey Dew Donuts are to the left of this) and it's the last door on left.
comment: Very clean and private

name: Boulder Public Library
directions: Located in the Boulder Public Library Children's Room (see comments). The library is between 9th and 11th streets and spans Boulder Creek (runs west to east) between Canyon Blvd. and Arapahoe Avenue. The Children's Room is just inside the Arapahoe Avenue entry.
comment: This is the family-use bathroom in the Boulder Public Library Children's Room, and generally used for caregivers and small children. For children's safety they require that people ask for the key, but as of May 29, 2007 the head Children's Librarian has instructed her staff that the key is to be provided to anyone who asks to use "the safe2pee bathroom." You can also simply say you are transgendered and uncomfortable using the other public bathrooms and they will provide the key.

name: FedEx Kinko's
comment: Call the store at 203-319-0500 for hours

name: The Ugly Mug
directions: down the back hallway
comment: it's a very small single stall bathroom. it is not wheelchair-accessible, but the entire cafe is very cool.

name: Subway
directions: Walk to the back. There will be two doors. Chose one.
comment: My favorite sub is chicken terryaki w/ lettuce, tomato, onions, and sweet onion sauce toasted on hearty italtian.

name: Hair Cuttery
directions: Walk straight in kind of quickly and walk towards the back. Pass the employees' lounge down the hallway that ends with a large door on the right. That is the bathroom.
comment: Jen is great for hair cuts! :]

name: Mattingly Brewing
directions: It's on the first floor, next to the bar. Accessible entry is through the back of the building, off the parking lot.
comment: http://mattinglybrewing.com/

comment: Gay, Lesbian, Bisexual, Transgender Student Support ServicesIndiana University705 E. 7th StreetBloomington IN 47408-3809PH: 812-855-4252 Fax: 812-855-4465 http://www.indiana.edu/~glbt/ Open Monday through Friday  8am to 5pm

name: Starbucks
directions: In the back of the store
comment: Don't require a key, baristas are nice and don't care if you don't buy something. Two bathrooms- both single occupant and both genderfree. Closes at 9.

name: TriCounty Mall
directions: First floor of the mall, near the store entrance to Macy's. It is a single-user lockable 'family' restroom off a small hallway kitty-corner from the  fountain and furniture area.
comment: Official hours are M-S 10-9, Sun 12-6, though the mall doors are generally open for an hour or two before and after the "official" hours.

name: Safeway
directions: Walk in on the left entrance and turn to the left 90 degrees. Wlk down the hallway a little bit and there will be two bathrooms: one for men and one for woman.
comment: Almost always open from 6:00 AM to 12:00 midnight except for holidays.

name: LGCCNO
directions: 1st Floor Available when the center is open.  Phone (504) 945-1103 to see if they are open.

name: Just Fresh
directions: Towards the rear of the restaurant, near where you pick up your orders.
comment: Website - http://www.justfresh.com/Open Mon-Fri 7 AM - 5 PM

name: Phoenix (Sky Harbor) Airport
directions: Family/Companion restroom across from gate C17.  I think there may be one at the beginning of each terminal, but I was only in terminal C.

name: Pasta Bangs!
directions: One single stall, non-gendered bathroom in rear of restaurant.
comment: Website: http://www.pastabangs.com/

name: Bare Bones Cafe
directions: 2 Single-Stall Gender-Neutral Bathrooms (labeled as such) in rear of coffee shop
comment: Website: http://www.muddywatersportland.com/

name: UBC Student Union Building
directions: North side of the second floor of the SUB

name: Charis Books & More
directions: This bathroom is towards the back-right of the store.
comment: Charis is Atlanta's independent feminist bookstore.The Charis employees range from ignorant-but-well-meaning to extremely-knowledgeable-and-helpful on trans/gender-varient issues.In my experience, this bathroom is one of the safest in the city for trans/gender-varient people to use._Store Hours_Monday  10:30 AM  -  6:30 PMTuesday  10:30 AM  -  6:30 PMWednesday  10:30 AM  -  8:00 PMThursday  10:30 AM  -  7:30 PMFriday 	10:30 AM  -  8:00 PMSaturday  10:30 AM  -  8:00 PMSunday  Noon  -  6:00 PM

name: Nugget Movie Theater
directions: Past the ticket booth and concession stand, at the end of the lobby.

name: Norwich Inn
directions: There's one bathroom at the far end of the tavern (Jasper Murdock's Alehouse), and one off the lobby.

name: Lebanon Food Coop
directions: Go through the entrance, straight past the info desk, then turn right at the Cafe and down the hall past the counter.  The bathroom is on the left.
comment: 7am-9pm, except major holidays

name: Hanover Food Coop
directions: Go straight through the entryway, then down the short corridor on your right, before the Produce section.  2 genderfree bathrooms.
comment: 8am-8pm (I think), closed on major holidays.

name: Lettieri Espresso and Bar
directions: Hidden by a pillar, all the way in the back.
comment: It's a lounge-y cafe, i cant see people questioning you if you just went in to use the washroom (and not to buy anything). Right in the village so there is usually less gender scrutiny.

name: Athletic Centre
directions: Go through the turnstyles at the equipment desk, down the stairs, make a left at the bottom, walk past the sports medicine clinic and they'll be on your right before you hit the pool.
comment: ok you need a pass or student id to get in, but you can sweet talk the equipment desk guys to let you in if you're savvy.

name: Baker Library
directions: Go into the stacks (open) and take the stairs or elevator to the sixth floor.  The restroom is near the elevator.

name: Juliano's
directions: All the way in the back of the resturaunt.
comment: This place has the advantage of weird hours (open to 1:30 am or 3:00 am depending on the day), but due to it's size it's impossible to slip in and out unnoticed just to use the bathroom... Not that you'd want to though, once you smelled the pizza.

name: Lou's Restaurant
directions: Walk along the counter to the back, through the doors to the kitchen, then down the stairs on your left.  Two bathrooms, both genderfree.

name: Hanover Inn
directions: Take the elevator or stairs up to the first floor, then follow the signs for 'Public Restroom'.

name: Come As You Are
directions: first door on your right, you can't miss it, it's huge.
comment: this is a sex shop - but very queer/woman/body/trans positive and polite :)

name: york university
directions: first floor, by the bakery/shwarma shop
comment: and oh its spacious!

name: Bay Park Square Mall
directions: In Food Court
comment: Family restroom
